<h1>CAVIAR</h1>
	<p>
		CAVIAR (CAusal Variants Identification in Associated Regions), a statistical framework 
		that quantifies the probability of each variant to be causal while allowing
		with arbitrary number of causal variants. 
	</p>
<p>CAVIAR was created by <a href="http://zarlab.cs.ucla.edu/group/">Farhad Hormozdiari</a>, 
			 <a href="http://zarlab.cs.ucla.edu/group/">Emrah Kostem</a>, 
			 <a href="http://zarlab.cs.ucla.edu/group/">Eun Yong Kang</a>,
			 <a href="http://bogdan.bioinformatics.ucla.edu/">Bogdan Pasaniuc</a> and 
			 <a href="http://www.cs.ucla.edu/~eeskin/">Eleazar Eskin</a> 
</p>

<h1>eCAVIAR</h1>
        <p>
                eCAVIAR (eQTL and GWAS CAusal Variants Identification in Associated Regions), a statistical framework
                that quantifies the probability of the variant to be causal both in GWAS and eQTL studies, while allowing
                with arbitrary number of causal variants.
        </p>
<p>eCAVIAR was created by <a href="http://zarlab.cs.ucla.edu/group/">Farhad Hormozdiari</a>,
                         <a href="http://www.broadinstitute.org/~asegre/">Ayellet V. Segre</a>,
                         <a href="http://www.well.ox.ac.uk/martijn-van-de-bunt">Martijn van de Bunt</a>,
			 <a href="https://www.broadinstitute.org/scientific-community/science/labs/getz-lab/current-lab-members">Xiao Li</a>,
			 <a href="http://zarlab.cs.ucla.edu/group/">Jong Wha J Joo</a>,
			 <a href="http://zarlab.cs.ucla.edu/group/">Michael Bilow</a>,
			 <a href="http://jaehoonsullab.semel.ucla.edu/">Jae Hoon Sul</a>,
                         <a href="http://bogdan.bioinformatics.ucla.edu/">Bogdan Pasaniuc</a> and
                         <a href="http://www.cs.ucla.edu/~eeskin/">Eleazar Eskin</a>
</p>

